  "name": "RPlog_Corellia_Corellia",
  "title": "Corellia, Corellia",
  "summary": "At the Coronet spaceport on Corellia, the retired Imperial pilot Antoine Dareus reconnects with the Twi'lek CorSec officer Twila, who offers him a position while he hunts for answers about his past and his old commander Darth Malign. They witness ISB Director Korynn Fleming brutally process captured rebel sympathizers and lock down the terminal, and the group is later joined by the medic Alina and the freshly landed Imperial pilot Krieg Inrokana, who reports to Commodore Caiton after a showboating flyby. The party adjourns to the Smugglers' Dig Cantina, where the bitter ex-Imperial starfighter pilot Gren Delede joins them and trades barbed war stories with Dareus, needling the Empire until the Imperial loyalist Wolf storms out in disgust. As the drinking deepens, Dareus reveals his disgraced history of imprisonment on Kessel and naked ambition, and Delede leaves Twila a blaster and a cutting parting remark about her place as an alien in the Empire. The night ends with Twila wounded and confused, Dareus shaken and unmoored, and their fragile friendship left in doubt.",
